This paper discusses a new index to quantify scientific achievement and leadership, which is relevant to several sub-fields of computer science. The paper mentions the use of databases and citation counts, which suggests a focus on digital libraries (cs.DL) and information retrieval (cs.IR). The concept of scientific leadership is also relevant to social informatics (cs.SI) and cybernetics (cs.CY). Finally, the paper discusses the coauthorship patterns of scientists, which could be relevant to cryptography (cs.CR) where collaboration and authorship are important factors.
